{% extends 'frontend_layout.html.twig' %}

{% block content %}
    <div class="row">
        <div class="card bg-dark text-white col-md-10 offset-md-1">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">
                    <a href="{{ path('frontend_static_page_how_to') }}">{{ 'How to'|trans }}</a> - {{ 'Routines'|trans }}
                </h5>
                <div>
                    You can visit "Routines" section by clicking <a href="{{ path('frontend_routine_index') }}"><i class="fas fa-sync"></i> {{ 'Routines'|trans }}</a> in navigation menu.
                </div>
                <br>
                <div>
                    Routines are core of this system. You can organize your life activities around them. At the begining you may limit yourself to two routines.
                    For example "Daily exercises" and "Work". Later when you will be more familiar with whole system you will add other routines that you would like
                    to train. For example you can add routine like "Night work" where you will perform things like writing or "Friday cleaning" that will
                    be your home cleaning routine.
                </div>
                <br>
                <div>
                    To add new Routine you need to click on <button class="btn btn-primary btn-sm"><i class="fas fa-sync"></i> {{ 'Create a routine'|trans }}</button>.
                    You need to provide a name of routine. Lets start with "Daily exercises". Type of routine should be "Sport". By default created routines are enabled.
                    If you will disable it you will not receive any reminders. You can also provide an optional description of the routine if you want - for excercises it could be
                    something like "My daily serie of push-ups". When you click on <button class="btn btn-primary btn-sm"><i class="fas fa-save"></i> {{ button_label|default('Save'|trans) }}</button>
                    your routine will be created.
                </div>
                <br>
                <div>
                    You can edit each routine created by yourself. You can change it's name, type, enabled state and description.
                </div>
                <br>
                <div>
                    Now when you visit "Routines" section by clicking <a href="{{ path('frontend_routine_index') }}"><i class="fas fa-sync"></i> {{ 'Routines'|trans }}</a> in navigation menu again you will see a list of your routines.
                    You can view more details about each routine when you click <button class="btn btn-primary btn-sm"><i class="fas fa-eye"></i> {{ 'Show'|trans }}</button> next to its name.
                </div>
                <br>
                <div>
                    Your next step should be creating a reminder. Please read more in <a href="{{ path('frontend_static_page_how_to_reminders') }}">{{ 'Reminders'|trans }}</a> documentation.
                </div>
                <br>
                <div>
                    <a href="{{ path('frontend_static_page_how_to_reminders') }}">{{ 'Reminders'|trans }}</a><br>
                    <a href="{{ path('frontend_static_page_how_to_completing_routines') }}">{{ 'Completing routines'|trans }}</a><br>
                    <a href="{{ path('frontend_static_page_how_to_notes') }}">{{ 'Notes'|trans }}</a><br>
                    <a href="{{ path('frontend_static_page_how_to_rewards') }}">{{ 'Rewards'|trans }}</a><br>
                    <a href="{{ path('frontend_static_page_how_to_goals') }}">{{ 'Goals'|trans }}</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
{% endblock %}

{% block title %}
    {{ parent() }} - {{ 'How to'|trans }} - {{ 'Routines'|trans }}
{% endblock %}
